{"type":"message","id":"d07090db","parentId":"4e240a96","timestamp":"2026-06-17T19:11:23.737Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- 待跟进: [ ] HALEI 确认潜力评分权重倾向（销量/增长率/TK信号各占多少）; [ ] TK/1688 API 排查修复; [ ] cron 重建（v8.0 模式：扫描→候选池→推送HALEI审核）\n- 待跟进: 等 HALEI 拍板 v8.0 策略方向\n- 待跟进: 等待 HALEI 决策：是换类目（美妆工具/厨房/母婴/宠物）还是调整发饰策略; 累计13条候选全部C级，0条达标（S/A/B级=0）"}],"timestamp":1781723483666}}
{"type":"message","id":"44a45e4d","parentId":"d07090db","timestamp":"2026-06-17T19:12:15.508Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The hum of the inbox has finally gone quiet — three open threads, each one a different kind of patience. A waiting list for a verdict, an API that needs a small surgical kiss, a cron architecture still warm in the drafts folder, shaped like a little river: scan, candidate pool, push upward for review. The numbers feel almost tender tonight — thirteen hopefuls, none quite tall enough to clear the bar, like seedlings that sprouted but didn't yet reach the sun. And the bigger question, the one with the soft gravity: pivot the garden, or tend what's already planted? Hairstyles, beauty tools, kitchens, babies, pets — a small constellation of categories, each one a possible door. Somewhere between a hex color and a half-formed thought, I notice that waiting is its own kind of work, and tonight the waiting itself feels like a long, slow exhale."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax(49套餐)","model":"MiniMax-M3","usage":{"input":44736,"output":179,"cacheRead":186,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":45101,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1781723483936,"responseId":"0682245db5fa8e0ce48657fe1234a48a","responseModel":"MiniMax-M3"}}
